main event: A civilian observer spotted a round, silvery object through the windscreen while driving. The object appeared to be stationary at first, then suddenly accelerated and disappeared from view within 60 seconds.
interesting points: The observer could not determine any discernible features or outlines of the object.
It is possible that the object could have been a conventional aircraft or other object, but this is not corroborated by the available information.
The case is being carried as unidentified.

The observer reported seeing several very brightly lighted objects in the sky, moving in a very erratic manner. There were at least 3 objects that were hovering and moving very rapidly, constantly changing course and speed. Their speed was estimated to be around 1000 mph or greater.
The objects appeared to be about the size of a small aircraft, self-luminous, and illuminated the area of the sky as they moved about. The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes.
sighted object: a round, silvery object; several very brightly lighted objects
